 Hello.. I want to thank you for taking the time to reading my post. I am looking for a roommate to move in this September 2014. I live in a 912 square foot (lot square footage= 7,253) 1 story, 3 bedroom, 1.5 bathroom, 2 carport house in Waipahu and currently the rent is $2000.00 a month. I can honestly say that this neighborhood is great, it`s quiet, safe, and it`s in a cul-de-sac. If you are truly interested I encourage you to ask the neighbors. The neighborhood is mostly families and retired people, so there is someone always home in the neighborhood. The house was built in 1962, but was recently updated Feb 2014. If you see the attached pictures you will see the appliances (brand new) in the center of the living room because they were re painting and re doing the floors which are ceramic tiling throughout. So if you like peace and quiet, this would be the house to move into. Like I mentioned earlier the house has three rooms, so I left the third room as a storage and you would be entitled to half of it. The house is partially furnished. Your room would be empty and I just have a dining table, chairs and a piano. I have no couches or side/coffee tables. I do have a TV that could be put in the living room, be we can figure all that out once that time comes. There would be one parking in the carport reserved for you. Guests can park in front of the house on the sidewalk.
 A little about myself. . . To be honest I didn`t want to post this on craigslist because of all the bad experiences I have had before and heard as well. Anyway I am a 30 year old female born and raised in California, but the Military (Navy) brought me here. So I work full time and a part time student at Hawaii Pacific University pursuing my nursing. I am not married nor do I have kids so if you happen to move in it would just be me and my two babies (doggies). I have one blue nosed pitbull, Sapphire and one Min pin and Jack russell mix, Kona both females and stay indoors (kennel trained). They are very loving sweet dogs and you would have to love them too if you moved in. They get along with other dogs well, so if you have pets, they are welcome!
 Anyway.. I work at the brig (military prison) so I work a crazy schedule. Every quarter I switch from days to nights 12 hour shifts and have every other weekend off. So the days I do work I am gone most of the day- and the times that I am off work- I like to enjoy my peace at home doing homework, studying or what not. If I have free time I usually take my dogs out walking, they love it and Kona doesn`t need a leach she just follows which is kind of cool. I love to cook so the kitchen is my thing. I live a very organized and neat/clean life- so keeping the house clean is a MUST. I don`t believe in wearing shoes in the house and every week I clean the house and my car. Call it OCD, but I like to live in a clean place and life. All I ask is respect of one another`s space and belongings. Also- being courteous is always good. For example- just giving me a heads up if someone is coming over whether I am home or not. I had a roommate that had a guy sleep over one night- so when I came home late one night there was some unknown guy sleeping on the couch and my roommate was not even home, whoa... AKWARD. Noise levels after hours are common sense as well. If it`s late I ask to keep noise at a minimum please. I am not really a party type person, if I ever do- that is what Waikiki is for. I don`t mind occasional get togethers because I may have them too occasionally. As for having significant others over- I don`t mind that they occasionally stay a night once in a while- but every night or very often is kind of pushing it, especially if they don`t help pay rent or the bills, let alone if they clean up our fridge if you know what I am saying ha ha. Oh and did I mention to keep the bedroom noises at a very minimum? Yes please that would be nice ha ha. I am pretty sure there is more I had to say here, but I can`t think of anything else major at the moment, so please if you have any questions, please ask. Please don`t think anything bad or negative towards my being open about roommates on here ha ha. I am really a nice person and easy to get along with :)
 I am pretty much open to any roommate, I DO NOT DISCRIMINATE :) I just had a couple check in the boxes that I had to cover to get an understanding of my potential roommate. If you are a serious inquiry, please email me an introduction of yourself, some what like the one I wrote here on CL. Thank you so much for taking the time to read this. Have a great and blessed day!
